### 1. Verify System Bank Account (ID 1) was seeded
GET http://localhost:8080/api/accounts/1
Accept: application/json

### 2. Create Alice's Account (SAVINGS, RON)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ownerName": "Alice Popescu",
  "iban": "RO47BTRLEURCRT0550023801",
  "currency": "RON",
  "accountType": "SAVINGS"
}

### 3. Create Bob's Account (CHECKING, EUR)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ownerName": "Bob Smith",
  "iban": "DE89370400440532013000",
  "currency": "EUR",
  "accountType": "CHECKING"
}

### 4. Fund Alice from the System Bank (10,000 RON)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceIban": "RO49AAAA1B31007593840000",
  "targetIban": "RO47BTRLEURCRT0550023801",
  "amount": 10000.00
}

### 5. Send money: Alice to Bob (Currency Conversion Test)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceIban": "RO47BTRLEURCRT0550023801",
  "targetIban": "DE89370400440532013000",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "idempotencyKey": "txn-alice-bob-001"
}

### 6. Test Idempotency (Run the exact same request again)
# Click play on this again. The response should be identical to Step 5,
# and Bob's balance should NOT increase a second time.
POST http://localhost:8080/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceIban": "RO47BTRLEURCRT0550023801",
  "targetIban": "DE89370400440532013000",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "idempotencyKey": "txn-alice-bob-001"
}

### 7. Check Alice's Ledger (Verify 2 transactions: 1 Deposit, 1 Transfer Out)
# Assuming Alice's Account ID is 2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/accounts/2/transactions
Accept: application/json

### 8. Test the 5,000 EUR Savings Limit (Should fail with 409 Conflict & "REJECTED")
POST http://localhost:8080/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceIban": "RO49AAAA1B31007593840000_ALICE",
  "targetIban": "DE89370400440532013000",
  "amount": 30000.00
}

### 9. Test Insufficient Funds (Should fail with 409 Conflict)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/transfers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sourceIban": "DE89370400440532013000",
  "targetIban": "RO49AAAA1B31007593840000_ALICE",
  "amount": 999999.00
}

### 10. Test Invalid IBAN Exception Handler (Should fail with 400 Bad Request)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ownerName": "Hacker",
  "iban": "",
  "currency": "RON",
  "accountType": "CHECKING"
}